GREENSBORO - Friday 's heavy rain gave way to a crisp sun-filled spring day Saturday when more than 300 people hopped in boats and kayaks for a 7 - mile trip down the Choptank River from Greensboro to Denton .
The trip began the fifth annual Paddlefest on the Choptank hosted by the Caroline County Chamber of Commerce .

RelatedSentence: The community event featured visitors from Michigan , Colorado , Virginia and West Virginia .
The number of kayakers has nearly doubled since 2012 when about 200 people participated in the event .
At the morning launch in Greensboro , Caroline County Commissioner Wilbur Levengood welcomed visitors to the event .
Levengood and his wife Sherry donated four bottles of Maryland wine as part of the event 's Poker Paddle .
